{"title_page": "Na\u0161a ognji\u0161ta", "text_new": "{{Infobox newspaper\n| name                 = Na\u0161a ognji\u0161ta\n| school               = \n| logo                 = \n| logo_size            = \n| logo_alt             = \n| image                = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = \n| motto                = \n| type                 = \n| format               = 23,5x33 cm\n| owner                = \n| founder              = \n| publisher            = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mostar-Duvno]]\n| president            = \n| editor               = \n| chiefeditor          = Robert Joli\u0107\n| depeditor            = \n| assoceditor          = \n| maneditor            = \n| generalmanager       = \n| newseditor           = \n| managingeditordesign = \n| dirinteractive       =\n| dirvisuals           =\n| dirvideo             =\n| campuseditor         = \n| campuschief          = \n| metroeditor          = \n| metrochief           = \n| opeditor             = \n| sportseditor         = \n| photoeditor          = \n| staff                = \n| foundation           = <!-- or |launched= --> <!-- Use: {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}, or {{start date|...}} if ceased -->\n| political            = \n| language             = [[Croatian language|Croatian]]\n| ceased publication   = <!-- Use: {{end date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| relaunched           = \n| headquarters         = \n| publishing_city      = [[Tomislavgrad]]\n| publishing_country   = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n| circulation          = 15 000\n| circulation_date     = 2014\n| circulation_ref      = \n| readership           = \n| sister newspapers    = \n| ISSN                 = \n| eISSN                = \n| oclc                 = \n| RNI                  = \n| website              = [http://www.samostan-tomislavgrad.info/index.php/nasa-ognjista-hrvatski-katolicki-mjesecnik samostan-tomislavgrad.info]\n| free                 = \n}}\n'''''Na\u0161a ognji\u0161ta''''' is a [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian-Croat]], [[Roman Catholic]], weekly newspaper published by the Franciscan province of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mostar-Duvno]] in [[Herzegovina]].  Following ''[[Glas Koncila]]'', the newspaper is the second most influental Catholic newspaper among  [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Croats]].<ref> [https://www.index.hr/vijesti/clanak/glas-koncila-i-nasa-ognjista-predlozeni-za-nagrade-ucipa/192716.aspx \"GLAS KONCILA\" I \"NA\u0160A OGNJI\u0160TA\" PREDLO\u017dENI ZA NAGRADE UCIP-a] ''index.hr''. Published 22 March 2004. Access date 14 April 2020. </ref> The newspaper is also distributed among the [[Croatian diaspora]] worldwide. The newspaper is printed in Franjo Kluz Printing House in [[Omi\u0161]], [[Croatia]].\n\nThe first issue was published at July 20, 1971, as the first Catholic periodical in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] following the ending of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina in the Second World War|Second World War]].<ref name=hrcak> Maji\u0107, M., 2007: [https://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=334827 NA\u0160A OGNJI\u0160TA \u2013 PRVI KATOLI\u010cKI LIST U BOSNI I HERCEGOVINI POSLIJE DRUGOGA SVJETSKOG RATA] ''Hum : \u010dasopis Filozofskog fakulteta Sveu\u010dili\u0161ta u Mostaru'' 2, 208-222. </ref> The newspaper wasn't published during the [[Bosnian War]] but was renewed following it's ending in 1995.\n\nNotable contributors include [[Jozo Ma\u0161i\u0107]], [[Ante Mati\u0107]], [[Nenad Mirko Novakovi\u0107]], [[Fabijan Lovri\u0107]], [[Bazilije Pand\u017ei\u0107]]...\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Newspapers in Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n\n[[Category:Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Tomislavgrad]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox newspaper\n| name                 = Na\u0161a ognji\u0161ta\n| school               = \n| logo                 = \n| logo_size            = \n| logo_alt             = \n| image                = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = \n| motto                = \n| type                 = \n| format               = 23,5x33 cm\n| owner                = \n| founder              = \n| publisher            = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mostar-Duvno]]\n| president            = \n| editor               = \n| chiefeditor          = Robert Joli\u0107\n| depeditor            = \n| assoceditor          = \n| maneditor            = \n| generalmanager       = \n| newseditor           = \n| managingeditordesign = \n| dirinteractive       =\n| dirvisuals           =\n| dirvideo             =\n| campuseditor         = \n| campuschief          = \n| metroeditor          = \n| metrochief           = \n| opeditor             = \n| sportseditor         = \n| photoeditor          = \n| staff                = \n| foundation           = <!-- or |launched= --> <!-- Use: {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}, or {{start date|...}} if ceased -->\n| political            = \n| language             = [[Croatian language|Croatian]]\n| ceased publication   = <!-- Use: {{end date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| relaunched           = \n| headquarters         = \n| publishing_city      = [[Tomislavgrad]]\n| publishing_country   = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n| circulation          = 15 000\n| circulation_date     = 2014\n| circulation_ref      = \n| readership           = \n| sister newspapers    = \n| ISSN                 = \n| eISSN                = \n| oclc                 = \n| RNI                  = \n| website              = [http://www.samostan-tomislavgrad.info/index.php/nasa-ognjista-hrvatski-katolicki-mjesecnik samostan-tomislavgrad.info]\n| free                 = \n}}\n'''''Na\u0161a ognji\u0161ta''''' is a [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian-Croat]], [[Roman Catholic]], weekly newspaper published by the Franciscan province of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mostar-Duvno]] in [[Herzegovina]].  Following ''[[Glas Koncila]]'', the newspaper is the second most influental Catholic newspaper among  [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Croats]].<ref> [https://www.index.hr/vijesti/clanak/glas-koncila-i-nasa-ognjista-predlozeni-za-nagrade-ucipa/192716.aspx \"GLAS KONCILA\" I \"NA\u0160A OGNJI\u0160TA\" PREDLO\u017dENI ZA NAGRADE UCIP-a] ''index.hr''. Published 22 March 2004. Access date 14 April 2020. </ref> The newspaper is also distributed among the [[Croatian diaspora]] worldwide. The newspaper is printed in Franjo Kluz Printing House in [[Omi\u0161]], [[Croatia]].\n\nThe first issue was published at July 20, 1971, as the first Catholic periodical in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] following the ending of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina in the Second World War|Second World War]].<ref name=hrcak> Maji\u0107, M., 2007: [https://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=334827 NA\u0160A OGNJI\u0160TA \u2013 PRVI KATOLI\u010cKI LIST U BOSNI I HERCEGOVINI POSLIJE DRUGOGA SVJETSKOG RATA] ''Hum : \u010dasopis Filozofskog fakulteta Sveu\u010dili\u0161ta u Mostaru'' 2, 208-222. </ref> The newspaper wasn't published during the [[Bosnian War]] but was renewed following it's ending in 1995.\n\nNotable contributors include [[Jozo Ma\u0161i\u0107]], [[Ante Mati\u0107]], [[Nenad Mirko Novakovi\u0107]], [[Fabijan Lovri\u0107]], [[Bazilije Pand\u017ei\u0107]]...\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:Tomislavgrad]]\n", "name_user": "Mudroslov", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Na%C5%A1a_ognji%C5%A1ta"}
{"title_page": "List of past Home and Away characters", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2013}}\n{{Refimprove|date=February 2020}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of past ''Home and Away'' characters}}\n''[[Home and Away]]'' is an Australian television soap opera that has been broadcast on [[Seven Network|Channel Seven]] since 1988. The following is an alphabetical list of all past characters that have been credited as regulars, with the actors who played them.\n\n{{Compact ToC|refs=yes|extlinks=yes|top=yes|sep='''&middot;'''|e=|g=|i=|q=|u=|x=|y=|z=|align=center}}\n\n==A==\n{| class=\"wikitable\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"250\" | Character\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"250\" | Actor(s)\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"300\" | Duration\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| [[Judith Ackroyd]] || [[Anna Hruby]] || 1999\u20132000 || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2013-08-28/prisoner-cell-block-h---what-happened-to-the-original-wentworth-prison-cast|title=What Happened to the original Wentworth Prison cast list?|first=Emma|last=Daly|date=28 August 2013|work=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Charlotte Adams (Home and Away)|Charlotte Adams]] || [[Stephanie Chaves-Jacobsen]] || 2001\u20132002 || <ref>{{cite magazine|last=Herbison|first=Jason|authorlink=Jason Herbison|title=Inside Oz|magazine=[[Inside Soap]]|date=14\u201327 September 2002|issue=214|pages=9}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tasha Andrews]]|| [[Isabel Lucas]]|| 2003\u20132006 || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newidea.com.au/isabel-lucas-home-and-away-best-career-advice|title=Home and Away\u2019s Isabel Lucas reveals life-changing news|date=16 September 2019|work=[New Idea]]|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Brad Armstrong (Home and Away)|Brad Armstrong]] || [[Chris Sadrinna]] ||  2006\u20132007 || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2007/07/summer-bay-c