. It is implied that he is romantically interested in her. [[Sarah Shahi]] stars as Tina Torres, an attractive teacher from [[Mexico]]. She is Alice's possible rival for Jeff's affections, though it seems Jeff prefers Alice. It is revealed in Episode 05 (\"Testing 1-2-3\") that she does not have her teaching [[license]], having gone to school, but taking jobs before she took her [[Final examination|finals]]. However, she stated later in the episode that she will be taking them.\n\n==Production==\nLike many American sitcoms, ''Teachers'' was shot before a studio audience.\n\nThe series began development under the title ''Filmore Middle'', which reflected its original [[middle school]] setting.\n\nThough adapted for American television by Matt Tarses, a writer and producer of the critically lauded series ''[[Sports Night]]'' and ''[[Scrubs (TV series)|Scrubs]]'', ''Teachers'' was panned by many critics (including the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'''s Tim Goodman) as unoriginal and clich\u00e9d. The show was quickly cancelled by NBC, the news coming on May 15.<ref>[http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds33066.html Television - News - 'Joey' axed as NBC unveils '06-07 schedule - Digital Spy<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Justin Bartha]] as Jeff Cahill\n*[[Sarah Alexander]] as Alice Fletcher\n*[[Phil Hendrie]] as Dick Green\n*[[Deon Richmond]] as Calvin Babbitt\n*[[Kali Rocha]] as Emma Wiggins\n*[[Sarah Shahi]] as Tina Torres\n*[[Matt Winston]] as Mitch Lenk\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#B6A7A7 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |aux2= |aux3= |airdate=|aux2T=U.S.<br>rating/share<br>(18-49) |aux3T=U.S. viewers<br>(million) |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=1\n |Title=Substitute\n |DirectedBy=[[James Burrows]]\n |WrittenBy=Matt Tarses\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|03|28}}\n |Aux2=3.3/8<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/04/04/nbc-primetime-results-for-the-week-of-march-27-april-2-20993/20060404nbc01/ |title=NBC Primetime Results for the Week of March 27-April 2 |publisher=[[NBC]] via TheFutonCritic.com |date=April 4, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |Aux3=6.71<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=040406_04 |title=WEEKLY PROGRAM RANKINGS FROM 03/27/06 THROUGH 04/02/06 |publisher=ABC Medianet |date=April 4, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=After 6 months of unrequited flirting Jeff hits on Tina, the substitute history teacher, in an attempt to make Alice jealous. Calvin and Dick concoct a scheme to ensure Alice does not get elected faculty chair. After rebuffing him most of the day Tina reciprocates and ultimately offers Jeff a one-night stand. Realising his feelings for Alice are serious Jeff makes up an excuse to end the date before things go too far. When Jeff understands that Alice doesn't want to date someone who treats teaching like a joke Jeff admits that he is embarrassed that he enjoys teaching and that is why he acts like he doesn't take his job seriously.\n |LineColor=b6a7a7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=2\n |Title=Field Trip\n |DirectedBy=[[Gail Mancuso]]\n |WrittenBy=Michael Lisbe & Nate Reger\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|04|04}}\n |Aux2=2.5/6<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/04/11/nbc-primetime-results-for-the-week-of-april-3-9-21066/20060411nbc01/ |title=NBC Primetime Results for the Week of April 3\u20139 |publisher=NBC via TheFutonCritic.com |date=April 11, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |Aux3=5.61<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=041106_04 |title=WEEKLY PROGRAM RANKINGS FROM 04/03/06 THROUGH 04/09/06 |publisher=ABC Medianet |date=April 11, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=b6a7a7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=3\n |Title=Schoolympics\t\t\n |DirectedBy=Gail Mancuso\n |WrittenBy=Ben Dougan & Robin Shorr\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|04|11}}\n |Aux2=2.4/6<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/04/18/nbc-primetime-results-for-the-week-of-april-10-16-21109/20060418nbc01/ |title=NBC Primetime Results for the Week of April 10\u201316 |publisher=NBC via TheFutonCritic.com |date=April 18, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |Aux3=5.19<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=041806_05 |title=WEEKLY PROGRAM RANKINGS FROM 04/10/06 THROUGH 04/16/06 |publisher=ABC Medianet |date=April 18, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=b6a7a7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=4\n |Title=Golf\n |DirectedBy=[[Gil Junger]]\n |WrittenBy=Matt Tarses\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|04|18}}\n |Aux2=2.2/5<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/04/25/nbc-primetime-results-for-the-week-of-april-17-23-21164/20060425nbc02/ |title=NBC Primetime Results for the Week of April 17\u201323 |publisher=NBC via TheFutonCritic.com |date=April 25, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |Aux3=4.50<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=042506_04 |title=WEEKLY PROGRAM RANKINGS FROM 04/17/06 THROUGH 04/23/06 |publisher=ABC Medianet |date=April 25, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=\n |LineColor=b6a7a7\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=5\n |Title=Testing\t\n |DirectedBy=Gil Junger\n |WrittenBy=Alison McDonald\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2006|04|25}}\n |Aux2=2.3/5<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2006/05/02/nbc-primetime-results-for-the-week-of-april-24-30-21229/20060502nbc02/ |title=NBC Primetime Results for the Week of April 24\u201330 |publisher=NBC via TheFutonCritic.com |date=May 2, 2006 |accessdate=November 5, 2010}}</ref>\n |Aux3=4.70<ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=050206_05 |title=WEEKLY PROGRAM RANKINGS FROM 04/24/06 THROUGH 04/30/06 |publisher=